This paper deals with the extension of Levesque's logic to the multi-agent case, which is a topic that falls under the sub-category of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also discusses the axiom system and semantics of the logic, which are topics related to Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO). Additionally, the paper deals with multi-agent systems, which falls under the sub-category of Multi-Agent Systems (cs.MA). The paper also discusses completeness proofs, which is a topic related to Programming Languages and Compilers (cs.PL). Finally, the paper deals with modal operators, which is a topic related to Computational Complexity (cs.CC).
